<TITLE> Cricket academies tri-nation series kicks off April 4 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 30 (bdnews24.com) -- The Grameenphone Academy Cup tri-nation series will kick off on April 4 at five different venues around the country. The national cricket academies of Bangladesh, Pakistan and South Africa will participate in the event, a press briefing was told at the sponsors head office in Gulshan Sunday. Dhaka, Jessore, Khulna, Chittagong and Bogra will host the matches over the five-week tournament, which is scheduled to finish on May 6. In addition to the one-day series, the three teams will also play four-day matches throughout the tournament. Bangladesh will take on South Africa in two four-dayers before the one-day series kicks off. The Bangladeshi team will also play two four-day matches against Sri Lanka after the one-day series has concluded. The South Africa Academy team are scheduled to arrive in Dhaka on April 1, while the Pakistan Academy team will arrive here on April 14. The Proteas will play their first four-dayer (April 4-7) in Jessore, and their second in Khulna (April 9-12) against the Bangladesh Academy squad. The fixtures will take place ahead of the one-day competition, which will get underway on April 15 in Chittagong. Except for the final, which will be on April 23 in the Mirpur Sher-e-Bangla National Stadium, all group matches in the tri-series will be held in Chittagong. The Pakistan Academy will play both their the four-day matches (April 26-29 and May 2-5) at the Shaheed Chandhu Stadium in Bogra. The tournament is a part of a five-year sponsorship deal between Grameenphone and the Bangladesh Cricket Board for the National Cricket Academy. Former Sri Lankan cricketers Ruan Kalpage and Champaka Ramanayeke have recently been given charge of the GP-BCB Cricket Academy, as head coach and fast bowling coach respectively. Khaled Mahmud, the former national captain and manager of operations at the GP-BCB Academy, announced a 14-member squad for the four-dayers against South Africa. The trio of pacers -- Rubel Hossain, Mahbubul Alam Robin and Sajedul Islam will replace pacers Dollar Mahmud, Nazmul Hossain and Talha Jubair after the first match. Academy squad: Naisruddin Faruk, (captain), Jahirul Islam, Imrul Kayes, Mehrab Hossain Jr, Shamshur Rahman, Naeem Islam, Nazmus Sadat, Mushfiqur Rahim, Dollar Mahmud, Talha Jubair, Nazmul Hossain, Enamul Haque Jr, Raihanuddin Arafat and Sohrawardi Shuvo. bd
